  • Method Details

    • updateAirline

      public abstract int updateAirline​(int id, java.lang.String newName, java.lang.String newAlias, java.lang.String newIATA, java.lang.String new_ICAO, java.lang.String newCallsign, java.lang.String newCountry, java.lang.String newActive) throws java.sql.SQLException
      Ensures validity of parameters, passes them into the updateAirline method of AirlineService.
      Parameters:
      id - The airline_id of the given airline you want to update.
      newName - The new name of the airline, may be "" if not to be updated.
      newAlias - The new alias of the airline, may be "" if not to be updated.
      newIATA - The new 2-letter IATA code of the airline, may be "" if not to be updated.
      new_ICAO - The new 3-letter ICAO code of the airline, may be "" if not to be updated.
      newCallsign - The new callsign of the airline, may be "" if not to be updated.
      newCountry - The new country of the airline, may be "" if not to be updated.
      newActive - The new active of the airline, "Y" or "N", may be "" if not to be updated.
      Returns:
      int The airline_id of the airline that was just updated by the AirlineService.
      Throws:
      java.sql.SQLException

    • updateAirport

      public abstract int updateAirport​(int id, java.lang.String newName, java.lang.String newCity, java.lang.String newCountry, java.lang.String newIATA, java.lang.String new_ICAO, java.lang.Double newLatitude, java.lang.Double newLongitude, java.lang.Integer newAltitude, java.lang.Float newTimezone, java.lang.String newDST, java.lang.String newTZ) throws java.sql.SQLException
      Ensures validity of parameters, passes them into the updateAirport method of AirportService.
      Parameters:
      id - The airport_id of the given airport you want to update.
      newName - The new name of the airport, may be "" if not to be updated.
      newCity - The new city of the airport, may be "" if not to be updated.
      newCountry - The new country of the airport, may be "" if not to be updated.
      newIATA - The new 3-letter IATA code of the airport, may be "" if not to be updated.
      new_ICAO - The new 4-letter ICAO code of the airport, may be "" if not to be updated.
      newLatitude - The new latitude of the airport, a string. Negative is South and positive is North. May be "" if not to be updated.
      newLongitude - The new longitude of the airport, a string. Negative is West and positive is East. May be "" if not to be updated.
      newAltitude - The new altitude of the airport in feet, a string. May be "" if not to be updated.
      newTimezone - The new timezone of the airport, hours offset from UTC. A string, may be "" if not to be updated.
      newDST - The new dst of the airport, one of E (Europe), A (US/Canada), S (South America), O (Australia), Z (New Zealand), N (None) or U (Unknown). May be "" if not to be updated.
      newTZ - The new tz_databaseTimezone of the airport, timezone in "tz" (Olson) format. May be "" if not to be updated.
      Returns:
      int The airport_id of the airport that was just updated by the AirportService.
      Throws:
      java.sql.SQLException

    • updateFlightEntry

      public abstract int updateFlightEntry​(int id, java.lang.String newLocationType, java.lang.String newLocation, int newAltitude, double newLatitude, double newLongitude)
      Ensures validity of parameters, passes them into the updateFlight method of FlightService.
      Parameters:
      id - The unique id of the given flight entry you want to update.
      newLocationType - The location type of the flight entry location, one of "APT", "VOR", or "FIX". May be "" if not to be updated.
      newLocation - The new location of the flight entry. May be "" if not to be updated.
      newAltitude - The new altitude of the flight entry in feet, a string. May be "" if not to be updated.
      newLatitude - The new latitude of the flight entry, a string. Negative is South and positive is North. May be "" if not to be updated.
      newLongitude - The new longitude of the flight entry, a string. Negative is West and positive is East. May be "" if not to be updated.
      Returns:
      int The unique id of the flight entry that was just updated by the FlightService.

    • updateRoute

      public abstract int updateRoute​(int id, java.lang.String newAirline, java.lang.String newSourceAirport, java.lang.String newDestAirport, java.lang.String newCodeshare, int newStops, java.lang.String newEquipment) throws java.sql.SQLException
      Ensures validity of parameters, passes them into the updateRoute method of RouteService.
      Parameters:
      id - The route_id of the given route you want to update.
      newAirline - The new 2-letter IATA or 3-letter ICAO code of the airline, may be "" if not to be updated.
      newSourceAirport - The new 3-letter IATA or 4-letter ICAO code of the source airport, may be "" if not to be updated.
      newDestAirport - The new 3-letter IATA or 4-letter ICAO code of the destination airport, may be "" if not to be updated.
      newCodeshare - The new codeshare of the route, "Y" or "N", may be "" if not to be updated.
      newStops - The new number of stops for the route, a string, may be "" if not to be updated.
      newEquipment - The new equipment for the route, may be "" if not to be updated.
      Returns:
      int The route_id of the route that was just updated by the RouteService.
      Throws:
      java.sql.SQLException
